<ITEM>It is natural for the per&s;on who has the misfortune of lo&s;ing old Friends, to be d<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;irous of making new ones.</ITEM>
<ITEM>Such a difference in temper and con&s;titution in two young Ladies as exclud<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">s all imaginary rival&s;hip, may be the cement of a firm Friend|&s;hip between them.</ITEM>
