<ITEM>&mdash; A light that, but in few of their hands, burns &s;teady, and often hurries the Sex into flight and ab&s;urdity; and, like other extremes, is hardly ever durable, <HI>Col. Morden.</HI></ITEM>
<ITEM>Ma<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">riage, which is the highe&s;t &s;tate of Friend&s;hip, generally ab|&s;orbs the mo&s;t vehement Friend&s;hip of female to female.</ITEM>
<ITEM>What female mind is capable of two fervent Friend&s;hips at the &s;ame time?</ITEM>
<ITEM>The following are the requi&s;ites, according to <HI>Col. Morden,</HI> of fervent and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">urable female Friend&s;hip; to wit, That both &s;hould [<HI>like Cla|ri&s;&s;a and Mi&s;s Howe</HI>] have enlarged hearts, a good education, and minds thir&s;ting after virtuous knowlege.&mdash;</ITEM>
