<ITEM><LIST>
<HEAD>Ma&s;ters. Mi&s;tre&s;&s;es. Servants.</HEAD>
<ITEM>Judgments of per&s;ons tempers are to be made by their dome&s;tic beha|viour, and by their treatment of their Servants.</ITEM>
<ITEM>Servants &s;hould take care, if there are any young Ladies where they live, how they make parties, or a&s;&s;i&s;t in clande&s;tine corre&s;pondencies.</ITEM>
